Jean Sharon Abbott was diagnosed with spastic diplegia , a form of cerebral palsy , when she was just four-years-old . 
  She suffered from muscle spasms, weakness and near immobility for three decades . 
  At the age of 33 she was diagnosed as having dopa-responsive dystonia (DRD), a rare muscle disorder that can be treated with a daily pill . 
  She insists she feels no resentment or anger about her life-changing diagnosis . 
 